prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Olive Scribble Sports Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Build the poster from one dominant diagonal action subject, one prop, and one abstract olive or yellow-green block.
- Use off-white paper ground, flat screenprint color slabs, heavy black ink silhouettes, chaotic scratch contours, red marker motion arcs, yellow-green dry-brush loops, and sparse diamonds or clipped debris.
- Keep the setting shallow, abstract, and editorial rather than realistic or scene-heavy.
- Use small rough hand-cut text only as a secondary poster accent, never as polished brand typography.
- Preserve imperfect elongated anatomy, cropped limbs, raw brush texture, and handmade print misregistration.

Avoid:
- {NEGATIVE_PROMPT}

Important content rule: match the extracted style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props, and new text, while avoiding the original soccer/overhead-kick source content.
